    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix channel allocation logic in random channel simulator\n\n### Summary\nThe `find_channel_desc_fromname()` function in the OAI channel simulator was not working correctly due to a bug in the channel allocation logic. When trying to create multiple channel models, only the first channel (at index 0) could be allocated, preventing subsequent channels from being created.\n\nThis happened because the loop in `new_channel_desc_scm()` that searches for available slots in the `defined_channels` array had incorrect logic - it would immediately trigger an AssertFatal when encountering any occupied slot, rather than continuing to search for the next available slot.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/TOOLS/random_channel.c`: Fixed channel allocation loop logic in `new_channel_desc_scm()` function to properly search for available slots before triggering allocation failure.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure multiple channel models with different names in the simulation\n2. Attempt to retrieve a channel model by name using `find_channel_desc_fromname()` \n3. Observe that only the first created channel can be found, subsequent channels return NULL even when they were successfully created\n4. This occurs because the channel creation logic only allocated channels to index 0, ignoring subsequent available slots in the `defined_channels` array\n\nThe fix ensures that multiple channel models can be properly allocated to different slots and retrieved by name.\n"
}